<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870515-0185 </DOCNO><HL> United Technologies UnitGets Helicopter Orders</HL><DD> 05/15/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> UTX FRESTAEROSPACE (ARO) </IN><DATELINE> HARTFORD, Conn.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   United Technologies Corp.'s Sikorsky Aircraft unit received an additional $200 million in orders for 25 military helicopters under a contract with the Australian Army.    The new orders for Sikorsky's S-70A9 Black Hawk run through 1990 and raise the total in the contract with Australia's army and navy to $600 million and 55 units. The diversified manufacturer also makes Pratt andamp; Whitney aircraft engines, Carrier air conditioners, Otis elevators, defense systems and aerospace gear. </TEXT></DOC>